    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for the house i'm buying in toronto. i've never heard of that before... what exactly is escrow and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow is a common practice in real estate transactions, particularly in Toronto, where it's required by law. An escrow account is a separate bank account managed by a third-party escrow agent, which holds funds until certain conditions are met. In the context of a home purchase, escrow typically covers property taxes and insurance, ensuring that these costs are paid periodically throughout the ownership period. This way, you're not left with a large bill at the end of the year, which can be a financial burden.",
